 ******************************* 

Donald Trump is an American businessman, television personality, and politician who served as the 45th President of the United States from January 20, 2017, to January 20, 2021. Born on June 14, 1946, in Queens, New York City, he became known for his real estate developments, including Trump Tower in New York City, and for hosting the reality TV show "The Apprentice."

Trump's political career began in earnest when he announced his candidacy for president in 2015 as a Republican. His campaign was marked by a populist message, strong stances on immigration, and a promise to "Make America Great Again." He won the presidential election in November 2016, defeating Democratic candidate Hillary Clinton.

During his presidency, Trump implemented significant tax cuts, withdrew the U.S. from the Paris Agreement on climate change, appointed three Supreme Court justices, and pursued an "America First" foreign policy. His presidency was also characterized by controversy, including two impeachment trialsâ€”one in 2019 related to the Ukraine scandal and another in 2021 related to the January 6 Capitol riot. He was acquitted by the Senate in both trials.

